  "text": "IL-15 drives T cell expansion and production of proinflammatory cytokines As previously mentioned, IL-15 is able to induce the production of different proinflammatory cytokines implicated in the pathogenesis of psoriasis . Moreover, IL-15 is a common  chain ( c ) cytokine and, similar to other  c cytokine members, IL-15 is involved in the survival and maintenance of T cells, especially memory CD8 + and, to a lesser extent, memory CD4 + T cells [CITATION_1] .",
